#: ../../../integrations/deployment/makeself.rst:4
msgid "Makeself"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/deployment/makeself.rst:6
msgid ""
"`Makeself <https://makeself.io>`_ is a small command-line utility to "
"generate self-extracting archives for Unix. It is pretty popular and it is "
"used by `VirtualBox <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/VirtualBox>`_ and `CMake "
"<https://cmake.org/download/>`_ projects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/deployment/makeself.rst:9
msgid ""
"Makeself creates archives that are just small startup scripts (*.run*, *."
"bin* or *.sh*) concatenated with tarballs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/deployment/makeself.rst:11
msgid "When you run such self-extracting archive:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/deployment/makeself.rst:13
msgid ""
"A small script (shim) extracts the embedded archive into the temporary "
"directory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/deployment/makeself.rst:14
msgid ""
"Script passes the execution to the entry point within the unpacked archive"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/deployment/makeself.rst:15
msgid "application is being run"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/deployment/makeself.rst:16
msgid "The temporary directory removed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/deployment/makeself.rst:18
msgid ""
"Therefore, it transparently appears just like a normal application execution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/deployment/makeself.rst:20
msgid ""
"With help of :ref:`deploy generator <deployable_deploy_generator>`, it's "
"only needed to invoke ``makeself.sh`` in order to generate self-extracting "
"archive for the further deployment:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/deployment/makeself.rst:23
msgid ""
"TMPDIR=`dirname $(mktemp -u -t tmp.XXXXXXXXXX)`\n"
"curl \"https://github.com/megastep/makeself/releases/download/release-2.4.0/"
"makeself-2.4.0.run\" --output $TMPDIR/makeself.run -L\n"
"chmod +x $TMPDIR/makeself.run\n"
"$TMPDIR/makeself.run --target $TMPDIR/makeself\n"
"$TMPDIR/makeself/makeself.sh $PREFIX md5.run \"conan-generated makeself.sh\" "
"\"./conan-entrypoint.sh\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/deployment/makeself.rst:31
msgid ""
"The ``PREFIX`` variable in the example points to the directory where binary "
"artifacts are situated. The ``md5.run`` is an output SFX archive:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/deployment/makeself.rst:33
msgid ""
"$ file md5.run\n"
"md5.run: POSIX shell script executable (binary data)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/deployment/makeself.rst:38
msgid ""
"The ``conan-entry-point.sh`` is a simple script which sets requires "
"variables (like ``PATH`` or ``LD_LIBRARY_PATH``):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/deployment/makeself.rst:40
msgid ""
"#!/usr/bin/env bash\n"
"set -ex\n"
"export PATH=$PATH:$PWD/bin\n"
"export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:$PWD/lib\n"
"pushd $(dirname $PWD/md5)\n"
"$(basename $PWD/md5)\n"
"popd"
msgstr ""

